  "why": "CrossASR does not perform iterative semantic mutations of seeds; instead it uses original texts as fixed ground-truth labels and synthesizes realistic audio via TTS for testing. The approach therefore preserves semantic consistency (the text is kept fixed and used as the oracle) and maintains naturalness (audio comes from real TTS engines) across iterations. The system also includes text preprocessing (normalization) to ensure correct TTS pronunciation and explicitly treats cases where the TTS likely produced invalid audio as indeterminable, rather than attributing failures to the ASRs. Because there is no per-iteration mutation that can accumulate drift, both semantic consistency and naturalness are enforced throughout the testing process.",
